ğŸ° Tower of Hanoi

ğŸ” Problem Statement:
You are given n disks stacked in increasing size on one rod (source).
Your goal is to move all disks to another rod (destination), using a helper rod â€” but:

You can only move one disk at a time.

A larger disk can never be placed on top of a smaller one.

ğŸ’» JavaScript Recursive Solution:
js
Copy
Edit
function towerOfHanoi(n, fromRod, toRod, usingRod) {
    if (n === 1) {
        console.log(`Move disk 1 from ${fromRod} to ${toRod}`);
        return;
    }
    towerOfHanoi(n - 1, fromRod, usingRod, toRod);
    console.log(`Move disk ${n} from ${fromRod} to ${toRod}`);
    towerOfHanoi(n - 1, usingRod, toRod, fromRod);
}

towerOfHanoi(3, 'A', 'C', 'B');
